<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-13T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-13T08:00:00-05:00" n="135" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d135">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/442</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-13T15:00:00+02:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">August 13, 1914, 3 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 16, 3:35 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>General mobilization has been ordered. Moratorium established.
                            Notwithstanding this all banks continue making cash payments in amounts.
                            Parliament adjourned till November. French and Austrian guardships have
                            departed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_MH1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgenthau</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>